HEADWORD: Cawk
<hw>Cawk</hw> <pr>(k⟦add⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>cauk</ets> limestone. A doublet of <ets>chalk</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An opaque, compact variety of barite, or heavy
spar.</def> <altsp>[Also written <er>cauk</er>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

